        public void loadAllTransparentBlocks(boolean clear)
        Takes the files specified by the preset list and the config and extract the transparent blocks Calling this will re-build the transparent block list.
        Parameters:

      • loadTransparentBlocks

        public boolean loadTransparentBlocks(FileConfiguration c,
                                     boolean clear)
        Loads the list of transparent blocks from a YAML file.
        Parameters:
        c - The file that will be loaded.
        clear - Whether or not the previous list of blocks will be cleared.
        Returns:
        Whether the file was successfully loaded; If it didn't contain the proper section it will return false This has nothing to do with whether any blocks that were loaded existed or not!

      • loadAllColors

        public void loadAllColors(boolean clear)
        Loads all the colors used by the map; The colors will be fetched from the config first, then the presets.
        Parameters:
        clear - Determines whether or not to clear the list of colors before reloading the new ones.

      • loadColors

        public boolean loadColors(FileConfiguration c,
                          boolean clear)
        Loads all colors from a YAML file.
        Parameters:
        c - The YAML file to load.
        clear - Whether or not to clear all the previous colors loaded.
        Returns:
        Whether this file contained a map color section; returning true does NOT mean that some materials did not exist

      • loadColor

        public void loadColor(Material m,
                      byte data,
                      Color c)
        Loads a color for the material and data value; This does NOT refresh the map.
        Parameters:

        data - The data value to set the new color for.
        c - The color that will represent the material and data value.

      • loadColor

        public void loadColor(Material m,
                      byte data,
                      int r,
                      int g,
                      int b)
        Loads a color for the material and data value, except it uses RGB values, not a color.
        Parameters:
        m - The material to set the new color for.
        data - The data value to set the new color for.
        r - The RED amount of the new color.
        g - The GREEN amount of the new color.
        b - The BLUE amount of the new color.

      • setColorAt

        public Color setColorAt(Location location)

        Parameters:
        location - The location to set the color.
        Returns:
        The previous color at the location provided; returns null if the location is not on the map.
